# Localization and TF

This folder contains the files related to localization and transform frame handling for the Robotics AI project.

Localization is important because the drone needs to know its position and movement inside the simulated environment. In this project, pose information from Gazebo is used to create ROS 2 odometry and TF data. This helps the rest of the system understand where the drone is located.

## Purpose of This Folder

The main purpose of this folder is to support the localization part of the drone simulation.

The Gazebo simulator provides pose information for the drone. This pose data is then converted into ROS 2-compatible odometry and transform frames. These frames allow other parts of the system, such as SLAM and control, to use the drone position correctly.

## Main Functionality

This folder focuses on:

- reading pose data from the simulator,
- converting pose data into odometry information,
- publishing transform frames,
- connecting the drone position with ROS 2 localization,
- supporting SLAM and mapping.

## Important Frames

The main TF frames used in this project are:

- `odom`
- `base_link`
- `link`

The localization node helps connect these frames so that the drone pose can be tracked properly.


